President Vladimir Putin of Russia has signed a law establishing administrative responsibility for violating the time and order for payment of goods (work, services) for public and municipal purposes.
The Act is intended to address the very acute problem of the employer ' s failure to fulfil its obligations in public and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation in which entrepreneurs were unable to pay for public and municipal contracts that had already been completed was widespread.
At that time, the President of Russia had instructed the Office of the Attorney General of the Russian Federation to take special control of the problem.
Because businessmen themselves were unable to cope with unfair customers who had entered into funded contracts, tried to evade the obligation to pay and included illegal terms in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in order to protect entrepreneurs ' rights to payment under public orders, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office has made 9,000 submissions, as a result of which 45,000 officials have been held disciplinaryly responsible, and 533 administrative officers have been prosecuted, 75 materials submitted to the investigating authorities for the conduct of the proceedings, and 46 of them have been prosecuted.
As a result, more than 66 billion roubles were owed to entrepreneurs.
These huge amounts were not accumulated as a result of the failure to pay multi-billion dollar contracts.
The Bosnian debt has resulted in numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs for much more modest amounts.
This is a typical case.
The manager of a small company won several million roubles to provide social transport services.
The person has invested all his working capital, has fully complied with the obligations, but has not received the amount of money in due course.
The result is a build-up of debts on salaries, taxes, loans that would lead to bankruptcy if the business did not seek assistance from the Public Prosecutor's Office.
The problem has now been maximized in a number of regions.
Nevertheless, as of the first half of 2017, the total public and municipal debt identified by the prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation was about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical levels, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office operates in manual crisis management.
The Attorney-General shall personally meet with local authorities to deal with all violations revealed by prosecutors and measures to remedy them without delay.
Such operational meetings have already been held this year in Yaroslavla and Yekaterinburg.
The Federal Act No. 189-FZ - amending the Code of Administrative Offences on Administrative Offences to establish administrative responsibility of the employer ' s officials for violating the time and procedure for payment of goods (work, services) in the execution of the purchase to provide for public and municipal needs - signed by the President of Russia last week.
The draft law was drafted by the Russian Ministry of Development on the initiative of the General Prosecutor ' s Office.
The new law would supplement the Code of Administrative Offences with an article that provided a fine of 30,000 to 50,000 roubles for infringement by an official of the time and procedure for payment of goods, works and services in public and municipal procurements.
If an official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he is expected to be disqualified for a period of between one and two years.
All prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure that these legislative innovations are applied in practice.
