In Ukraine, Russians were invited to be sent to prison for illegally crossing the border
The Supreme Council of Ukraine has a draft law under which Russians may be punished for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
As reported by RT TV, an electronic data base in the Ukrainian Parliament involves a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to illegally enter the country.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If, on the other hand, the perpetrator was detained on the border with weapons, he would be detained for up to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians attempting to enter Russia outside designated crossing points.
